Docker commands:
->Docker ls - to list all docker containers
->docker network ls -> to liss all networks
->docker run -d --name login nginx:latest -creates docker container with nginx image
->docker exec -it login /bin/bash
  docker exec: Executes a command inside a running container.
  -it: Flags to run interactively (-i for interactive, -t for allocating a pseudo-TTY).
  <container-name-or-id>: The name or ID of the running container (e.g., test).
  /bin/bash: The command you want to run inside the container. In this case, it opens a Bash shell.
-> apt-get install iputils-ping -y - to install ping
